2002-08-16 Friday 22:54  Roberto Bagnara <bagnara@cs.unipr.it>

	* NEWS (1.31), interfaces/C/ppl_c.cc (1.43), interfaces/C/ppl_c.h
	(1.43), interfaces/C/lpenum/lpenum.c (1.14): The functions taking
	non-const arguments named ppl_new_<T>_from_<S> have been renamed
	ppl_new_<T>_recycle_<S>, where <T> is either "C" or "NNC", and <S>
	is either "ConSys" or "GenSys".  The old names have been given to
	the new const functions.

