2002-07-29 Monday 00:43  Enea Zaffanella <zaffanella@cs.unipr.it>

	* tests/universe6.cc (1.2): Added a new test, showing two bugs:  -
	the first bug has to do with an invariant that was not fullfilled  
	 when creating an NNC polyehdron starting from an empty constraint
	system;    this bug was only visible when compiling with assertions
	turned on.   - the second bug was due to the fact that
	check_universe() returns     the wrong result when applied to a
	zero-dim-universe polyhedron.

