2002-06-07 Friday 16:40  Roberto Bagnara <bagnara@cs.unipr.it>

	* interfaces/Prolog/: exceptions.hh (1.5), ppl_prolog.icc (1.35):
	The function term_to_polyhedron_handle() replaces get_ph_pointer().
	 The new function either return a plausible polyhedron handle or
	throws the `not_a_polyhedron_handle' exception.  All sites that
	used to call get_ph_pointer() have been consequently simplified.

