2001-12-12 Wednesday 17:16  Elisa Ricci <ericci@cs.unipr.it>

	* src/: Polyhedron.cc (1.96), Polyhedron.inlines.hh (1.11): The
	function Polyhedron::set_zero_dim_univ() is now in Polyhedron.cc
	(instead of Polyhedron.inlines.hh), says that a zero-dimensional
	polyhedron is in a 0-dimensional space and clears the system of the
	polyhedron.  Used "space_dim" instead of "space_dimension()" (where
	we call this function many times).

